@node "Features" "Features"
              @{b} @{fg highlight}YAAV Feature List:@{ub}@{fg text}
               @{b}@{u}@{fg shadow}@{bg shine}==================@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}@{bg back}

   @{b}@{fg fill}@{bg shine}*@{ub}@{fg text}@{bg back} @{b}Font-sensitive GadTools interface.@{ub}

   @{b}@{fg fill}@{bg shine}*@{ub}@{fg text}@{bg back} @{b}Non-strict parsing of Autodoc structure.@{ub}
      - This enables the parsing of Autodocs that don't adhere strictly to the
      standard

   @{b}@{fg fill}@{bg shine}*@{ub}@{fg text}@{bg back} @{b}Parsing cache for faster viewing.@{ub}

   @{b}@{fg fill}@{bg shine}*@{ub}@{fg text}@{bg back} @{b}Document lists for faster selection of autodocs@{ub}

   @{b}@{fg fill}@{bg shine}*@{ub}@{fg text}@{bg back} @{b}HyperLinking@{ub}
      - By clicking on function names within the Doc Viewer window you
      automatically go to the related Autodoc page

   @{b}@{fg fill}@{bg shine}*@{ub}@{fg text}@{bg back} @{b}Cross-Reference facility@{ub}
      - by enabling the related feature, all references to functions or include
      files will be HyperLinked to the corresponding documents! This includes
      Function names, include filenames and system constants defined in include
      files.

   @{b}@{fg fill}@{bg shine}*@{ub}@{fg text}@{bg back} @{b}Dictionary@{ub}
      - by enabling this feature you can find references to System structures or
      constants within include files. Simply click on a name in the viewer
      window and, PRESTO! :)

   @{b}@{fg fill}@{bg shine}*@{ub}@{fg text}@{bg back} @{b}Retrace@{ub}
      - 256-item history list

   @{b}@{fg fill}@{bg shine}*@{ub}@{fg text}@{bg back} @{b}Commodity@{ub}
      - Full commodity interface
